1 6-3-1010 by creating a new subsection (b) and
2 23-6-206(a)(intro) and (iii) are amended to read:
3
4 6-3-1002. Cruelty to animals.
5
6 (b) Any person who intentionally injures or disables
7 a predatory animal as defined by W.S. 23-1-101(a)(viii) by
8 use of an automotive vehicle, motor-propelled wheeled
9 vehicle, or vehicle designed for travel over snow shall
10 upon inflicting the injury or disability immediately use
11 all reasonable efforts to kill the injured or disabled
12 predatory animal. Any person who fails to immediately use
13 all reasonable efforts to kill an injured or disabled
14 predatory animal as required by this subsection commits
15 cruelty to animals.
16
17 6-3-1004. Penalties; misdemeanor offenses.
18
19 (a) A first offense of cruelty to animals or of a
20 violation of W.S. 6-3-1003 is a misdemeanor punishable by
21 imprisonment for not more than six (6) months, a fine of
22 not more than seven hundred fifty dollars ($750.00) one
23 thousand dollars ($1,000.00), or both.
