2 (c) In addition to any penalty provided by this
3 section, for a conviction of a violation of W.S.
4 6-3-1002(b), a court may revoke any license, suspend a
5 person's privilege to purchase or receive any other license
6 or to take any wildlife pursuant to W.S. 23-6-206.
7
8 6-3-1010. Impounding and forfeiture hearing;
9 enforcement.
10
11 (b) In addition to any other peace officer with
12 authority to enforce this article, game and fish law
13 enforcement personnel qualified pursuant to W.S. 9-1-701
14 through 9-1-707 are authorized to enforce the provisions of
15 W.S. 6-3-1002(b) and 6-3-1004.
16
17 23-6-206. Revocation of license; hunting after
18 suspended license.
19
20 (a) The court may, in its discretion, revoke any
21 license issued under this act to any person convicted of a
22 violation of this act or W.S. 6-3-1002(b), for the
23 remainder of the year in which the conviction occurs, and
